<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">Your innate health and power regeneration rates are percentage-based off your total health and power.  Food and drink grant fixed bonuses to your health (food) and power (drink) regeneration rates.
<br />

<br />
Tier 2 food and drink is made by level 10+ craftsman from Antonica and Commonlands harvests.  You need 20+ Fishing and Gathering to make these foodstuffs.
<br />

<br />
The Power regeneration is especially noticeable when doing tradeskills.  If you cast tradeskill arts preemptively or get unlucky with a few catastrophes that drain your Power, having Tier 2 drink makes a huge difference in your ability to make quality and high quality (as opposed to poor and standard quality) tradestuffs.
<br />

<br />
The quality of your food and drink does not affect your regeneration rates while in combat.  You must rely on spells like Breeze and Regrowth to boost your regeneration rates in those situations.
<br />

<br />
The effects required to get these regeneration rates are bugged.  If you set yourself to auto-eat and auto-drink (Eat while Hungry and Drink while Thirsty) and this event occurs while you are in combat or making a tradeskill recipe, the effect will fade and <span style="font-weight: bold">not</span> refresh.  You will then be forced to force-feed yourself to get the effect again.  This happens a lot, and if you notice your group mates are continually low on health or power after combat, ask them to make sure their Meal and Drink effects are still active.</span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Provender on Mon Jan 24, 2005 2:09 pm; edited 4 times in total</span></td>
</td></tr>
<br />
